quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  40,21,"Do they not travel through the earth and see what the end of those before them was? They were superior to them in strength, and in the traces they have left in the land, but God called them to account for their wrongdoing, and they had none to defend them against God"
  40,22,"That was because there came to them their messengers with guidance, but they rejected them. So God called them to account, for He is Full of Strength, Strict in Punishment"
  40,23,Indeed We sent Moses with Our signs and a manifest authority
  40,24,"To Pharaoh, Haman, and Qarun, but they called him a deceiver telling lies"
  40,25,"Now when he came to them in truth from Us they said, “Slay the males of those who believe with him, but keep alive their females.” But the plots of unbelievers end in nothing but error"
  40,26,"Pharaoh said, “Leave me to slay Moses, and let him call on his Lord. What I fear is that he should change your way of life, or that he will cause problems to appear in the land.”"
  40,27,"Moses said, “I have indeed called upon my Lord and your Lord for protection from every arrogant one who does not believe in the Day of Account.”"